PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784287145
OL,3,CWildfire stretching nearly four miles
OL,4,Ccontained in UK's largest national park
OL,6,FThe Scottish government's Justice
OL,7,FSecretary Neil Gray, who has
OL,8,Fresponsibility for resilience within
OL,9,Fhis portfolio, said the decision to
OL,10,Fevacuate campsites and other
OL,11,Fproperties nearby had been taken as a
OL,12,Fprecaution.
OL,14,FHe said: "This wildfire in the
OL,15,FCairngorms National Park is currently
OL,16,Fcontained thanks to the exceptional
OL,17,Fwork of firefighters who have been on
OL,18,Fthe scene since Wednesday morning.
OL,26,@vD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784287145
OL,3,CWildfire stretching nearly four miles
OL,4,Ccontained in UK's largest national park
OL,6,F"Public safety is the priority, which
OL,7,Fis why the decision to evacuate a
OL,8,Fcampsite and various properties has
OL,9,Fbeen taken as a precautionary measure.
OL,11,F"I want to thank the firefighters,
OL,12,Fpolice, land managers, volunteers and
OL,13,Fall partners who are doing an
OL,14,Foutstanding job keeping people,
OL,15,Fproperty and the natural environment
OL,16,Fas safe as possible.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784287145
OL,3,CWildfire stretching nearly four miles
OL,4,Ccontained in UK's largest national park
OL,6,F"The Scottish government continues to
OL,7,Fmonitor the situation closely and the
OL,8,FScottish Fire and Rescue Service has
OL,9,Fconfirmed they have adequate resources
OL,10,Fcommitted to this incident."
OL,12,FSome locals expressed concerns that
OL,13,Ftourists were still trying to access
OL,14,Fthe area despite road closures being
OL,15,Fin place.
OL,17,FOne local woman, who wished to remain
OL,18,Fanonymous, said: "The absolute
OL,19,Fselfishness of tourists ` isn't that
OL,20,Finsane?
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@\O]zD@ROU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1784287145
OL,3,CWildfire stretching nearly four miles
OL,4,Ccontained in UK's largest national park
OL,6,F"'There's a fire but we still want to
OL,7,Fgo to Loch Morlich' ` I think it's
OL,8,Fjust ignorance."
OL,10,FShe added: "It's like going to
OL,11,Fsomewhere in America during tornado
OL,12,Fseason.
OL,14,F"You know what you're getting into."
OL,16,FIan McMeekin, head of prevention at
OL,17,Fthe Scottish Fire and Rescue Service
OL,18,F(SFRS), said they expect to be at the
OL,19,Fscene for the rest of the day and that
OL,20,Fit is too early to determine what may
OL,21,Fhave caused the fire.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@PO]rD@LOUvD@AOUvD@dO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
